                <h3>Buy and Sell Rules</h3>

                <h4>Sell Trade Entry Rules:</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Check Trend:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>On the 4-hour chart, ensure the SMMA channel is below the middle Bollinger Band, indicating a downtrend.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Identify Resistance Area:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>On the 30-minute chart, wait for price to approach a resistance area.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Check for Price Action Patterns or Divergence:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>If no price action patterns are present, check for divergence between Price and the CCI/BB/SMMA window on the 30-minute chart.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Confirm Volume:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Ensure high volume with the Volume bar forming significantly higher or consecutively higher peaks.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Enter Trade:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Enter a new trade position as soon as the candlestick pattern or divergence pattern has completed.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Set Stop Loss:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Place stop loss above the most recent swing high.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Trail Stop Loss:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Use the SMMA channel or middle Bollinger Band to trail the stop. Alternatively, exit manually when the Bollinger Band on the CCI begins to contract.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ol>

                <h4>Buy Trade Entry Rules:</h4>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Check Trend:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>On the 4-hour chart, ensure the SMMA channel is above the middle Bollinger Band, indicating an uptrend.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Identify Support Area:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>On the 30-minute chart, wait for price to approach a support area.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Check for Price Action Patterns or Divergence:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>If no price action patterns are present, check for divergence between Price and the CCI/BB/SMMA window on the 30-minute chart.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Confirm Volume:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Ensure high volume with the Volume bar forming significantly higher or consecutively higher peaks.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Enter Trade:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Enter a new buy trade position as soon as the candlestick pattern or divergence pattern has completed.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Set Stop Loss:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Place stop loss below the most recent swing low.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Trail Stop Loss:</strong>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Use the SMMA channel or the middle Bollinger Band to trail the stop. Alternatively, exit manually when the Bollinger Band on the CCI begins to contract.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ol>

